<h1> First Steps </h1>
<br>



<h2> Switch between views </h2>
Swipe <br>
across the tab bar <br>
click <i>nav</i> at the top, for a <b>dialog box</b>, or click <b>?</b> on bottom.
<br> <br>
The current learning verse remains.
<br> <br>
<br> <br>



<h2> Home </h2>
<p>
Here you can select a verse and then <i>go</i> to a learning method. <br>
<br>

</p>
<!-- <br> <p></p> <a href=''> </a> <h1> </h1> <i> </i> <b></b> <h2> </h2> -->

<p>
The Speak button is TTS, and Opt switches to the system settings for it. <br>
<br>
The search button searches in the verse field (e.g., John 3) and in the verse text field. <br>

</p>
<h3> Memorization Verse </h3>
<p>
The memory verse can be activated for learning: <br>
Current verse with <i>button</i> <br>
--> to <b>"Memorization Verse"</b> -with- <i>button</i> --> to current verse. <br>
</p>
<br> <br>
<br> <br>
<!-- <br> <p></p> <a href=''> </a> <h1> </h1> <i> </i> <b></b> <h2> </h2> -->



Learning Method
<h2> Word Click </h2>
<p>
It's clear that you can click on the word. <br>
Also included is the option of setting <i>Speech to Text</i> to "easy to recognize"
</p>
<br> <br>
<br> <br>


Learning Method
<h2> Word Mixing</h2><br>
<p>
Click on the word, then click again on the space where it should go. <br>
(If correct, it <i>jumps</i> to the correct place) <br>
</p>
<br> <br>
<br> <br>


Learning Method
<h2> Letters</h2><br>
<p>
Click on the blue or orange letter fields. <br>
Below you can see the moves, e.g., 5 | 20 <br>
5 moves by users of at least 20. <br>
</p>
<!-- <br> <p></p> <a href=''> </a> <h1> </h1> <i> </i> <b></b> <h2> </h2> Translated-->

<br> <br>
<br> <br>


<h2> Speaking </h2><br>
<p>
Here you can learn by heart. <br>
Requires TTS text to speech and speech recognition. <br>
<br>
Part of the verse text can also be learned by tapping the word (from-to). <br>
<br>
All this with many setting options.
</p>
<br>
<br> <br>


Page
<h2> Discover </h2><br>
<p>
Above, there is a random verse that can be set. <br>
via "Opt"<br>
There you can also search for words in the Bible, which are then saved as a list.<br>
With the JSON list format, the same verse can be displayed multiple times. <br>
With others, only once. Here, the "list" remembers each verse viewed.<br><br>
The list can be displayed individually via <b>Word List</b>. With a memory function.
</p>
<br>
<p>
</p>
